summary: PlayStation Network (PSN) experienced a widespread outage that lasted for nearly a day, affecting users globally. The outage prevented gamers from signing into their accounts and playing online multiplayer games. Some reports indicated that even single-player games and disc drives were affected. As the outage persisted, complaints and concerns from frustrated users surged, with many expressing their exasperation and disappointment. Despite efforts to resolve the issue, the exact cause of the outage remained unknown. After approximately 20 hours, PSN services began to gradually come back online, restoring access to online features and digital content for users worldwide.
